      "content": {
        "title": "Fat Embolism and Second-Hit Phenomenon",
        "definition": "Systemic inflammatory response after long-bone fixation in unstable patients causing ARDS and coagulopathy.",
        "summary": "Early IM nailing of femur in stable patients is safe; delay when physiologically deranged."
      },
